The Somali-American congresswoman from Minnesota, Ilhan Omar, has retained her seat in the US Congress for the Democrats, winning 64.6% of the vote against the 25.9% of her closest contender, Republican Lacy Johnson. Speaking to the BBC after her victory, Omar said her success would mean a lot to young men and women. She said her opposition to US President Donald Trump would go on if he was re-elected. --BBC--